Epistolae ad diuersos p. 666. Anderlecht. . HN: Loncl. xvii. 26: LB. 606. (c. 5 July ‘?> 1521.

[Between the Diet of Worms (l. 88) and the publication of F. The numerous resemblances to Ep. 1218 suggest that this letter is of the same date. The resemblances to Ep. 1195 are also striking3 but the difference of date is shown by the statements about Luther's acknowledgement of his own books (cf. 1. 88 with Ep. 1195. 69—70).

With Ep. 1228 this letter is appended to the Strasburg editions of Henry V111's Assertio, 9 Aug. and 7 Sept. 1522 (see Ep. 1227. 511). the latter being a translation into German by Murner (Ep. 1397. 2611) ; but as there is no variation in either of them, Grieninger was no doubt reprinting from F. For Murner's transla- tions see the Weimar edition of Luther‘s Werke, x, pt. 2, pp. 175·6; and, for their character, cf. Ep. 1228. 25, 58n.]
